comments: I emailed him asking about sources for a Classics paper. I was expecting a couple sources a couple days after I sent the initial email professors have lives too, you know? He replied twenty minutes later with nearly a dozen relevant sources, ranging from super official academic papers to blog posts that he enjoys on the topic.

comments: Diamond is hands down one of the best profs I\'ve had in my university career. He cares a lot about what he\'s teaching and who he teaching it to, and his take on ancient philosophy is always insightful, inspiring, and accessible. If you have the chance to take a course with him, do, you won\'t regret it.

comments: He is an incredible person and a brilliant man, one can learn a lot from him. If you take his class be prepared to work your ass off, he expects a lot from his students but in an encouraging way. If you put the work in and really try to understand what he means, you will get more than a grade from this class, which is the whole point.

comments: Dr. Diamond is an intelligent individual who has a deep passion for the materials in his course! He is a fair grader, setting clear expectations and is incredibly engaged with the class. The issues I found, however, is that there are WAY too many textbooks and I felt as though the course was more like a drama class than an analysis of politics.

comments: His criticisms of written work were often vague and incomprehensible. On one such occasion, when asked to elaborate, he couldn\'t remember what he\'d meant to say about my paper. His tests and quizzes are tough, and don\'t often relate to the work. He tested us based on his own personal opinion, as well as the opinions of other students in the class.

comments: He\'s a great guy and a great teacher. I\'ve had him for two classes and he is always enthusiastic during lectures and friendly during office hours: it is clear that he cares about both his students and the class material. One tip: his quizzes and tests are easy, most of the questions are based on facts (names, places, people, etc.).
